    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="761"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d761">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-13T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. Department’s August 9, 5 p.m.<note n="50" xml:id="d761fn50">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_737">p. 737</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>American Senate feared that Mexico would be heartened by Colombia’s attitude and
                    would be more persistent in forcing her plan of nationalization of oil lands on
                    the ground that it was justifiable as proven by Colombia’s action. That this
                    belief has foundation is shown by a telegram from American Embassy, Mexico City,
                    which states: “Local press today features Associated Press report that Colombia
                    has declared petroleum producing lands the property of the Government.” If
                    Colombia enforces nationalization we must expect other Latin American countries
                    to follow suit and this should be averted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
